  "prompt": "Just found out autistic roommate\u2019s last address was a low income housing complex that help tenants get into real life, and now he is living with me?",
  "response": "It sounds like you\u2019re navigating a complex situation with your autistic roommate. Living with someone who has experienced challenges related to income or housing can require extra understanding and patience. Here are a few tips on how to approach this:\n\n1. **Open Communication:** Have an open and honest conversation with your roommate about their needs and expectations. It\u2019s important to establish clear boundaries and mutual respect from the start.\n\n2. **Understanding Needs:** Recognize that autistic individuals may have specific needs related to their routines, sensory sensitivities, or moments when they need space. Ask your roommate about what helps them feel comfortable in a shared living situation.\n\n3. **Support Structure:** Since your roommate has recently transitioned from a low-income housing complex, they may be adjusting to new routines and responsibilities. Consider discussing any support systems they may be involved with and how you can navigate this transition together.\n\n4. **Be Patient:** Adjusting to living with someone new can be a challenge for both parties. Be patient as both of you navigate living in a shared space.\n\n5. **Establish House Rules:** Together, create a set of house rules that respect both your needs and preferences, covering things like cleaning responsibilities, shared space usage, and quiet times.\n\n6. **Resources:** If your roommate is open to it, you can help them find resources for support, social activities, or networking opportunities that can further assist in their transition and growth.\n\n7. **Set Up a Code of Conduct:** Develop a guide for communication and conflict resolution in case disagreements arise. Knowing how to address issues when they come up can help maintain a healthy living dynamic.\n\nAbove all, empathy and communication are key. Your roommate may have strengths and insights that can lead to a rewarding living arrangement for both of you.",
